1️⃣ orders (FACT TABLE)

Grain: 1 row per order

column	type	notes
order_id	INT	primary key
customer_id	INT
dasher_id	INT
restaurant_id	INT
city_id	INT
order_created_ts	TIMESTAMP	order placed time
order_picked_ts	TIMESTAMP	optional
order_delivered_ts	TIMESTAMP	optional
order_status	VARCHAR	CREATED, PICKED, DELIVERED, CANCELLED
order_amount	DECIMAL	revenue

2️⃣ customers (DIM)
column	type
customer_id	INT
signup_date	DATE

3️⃣ dashers (DIM)
column	type
dasher_id	INT
city_id	INT
signup_date	DATE

4️⃣ restaurants (DIM)
column	type
restaurant_id	INT
city_id	INT
restaurant_name	VARCHAR

5️⃣ cities (DIM)
column	type
city_id	INT
city_name	VARCHAR

🧠 PRACTICE QUESTIONS (INTERVIEW STYLE)
🟢 EASY (Warm-up)
Q1

For each city, find the total number of delivered orders.

Q2

For each day, find:

number of orders created

number of orders delivered

Q3

For each restaurant, find the total revenue from delivered orders.

🟡 MEDIUM (Most common)
Q4

Find the top 3 restaurants by revenue in the last 30 days.

Q5

For each dasher, find the total number of delivered orders.

Q6

For each city and day, calculate the average delivery time
(order_delivered_ts - order_created_ts) for delivered orders.

Q7

Find dashers who delivered more than 5 orders in a single day.

🔴 HARD (Window + Analytics)
Q8 ⭐

For each city and day, calculate the day-over-day change in delivered orders.

Q9 ⭐

For each dasher, calculate a 7-day rolling count of delivered orders
(MySQL compatible).

Q10 ⭐

Find restaurants that had orders created but zero delivered orders in the last 14 days.

🔴 HARD (Business / Funnel)
Q11 ⭐

For each city, calculate:

total orders created

total orders picked

total orders delivered

delivery rate (% delivered / created)

Q12 ⭐

For each city, find the top dasher based on
average deliveries per active day.

🔴 VERY HARD (Real Interview Favorites)
Q13 ⭐⭐⭐

Calculate the 90th percentile delivery time per city
(MySQL – no percentile function).

